# AGENTS.md

## Purpose

**Product design and frontend prototyping project.** Focus on visual fidelity and rapid iteration.

Not production code — ignore scale, security, backend, and deployment concerns.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router, Turbopack) + React 18 + TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS + Arbor Design System (`@linktr.ee/arbor`, `@linktr.ee/design-tokens`)
- Phosphor Icons (`@phosphor-icons/react`) + Radix UI primitives
- Framer Motion for animations

## Setup & Commands

```bash
# First time: npm login for @linktr.ee packages, then:
yarn setup

# Development
yarn dev      # localhost:3000 (Turbopack)
yarn build    # Type-check and build
yarn lint     # ESLint
yarn format   # Prettier
```

## Data & State

**Mock data** lives in `lib/`:
- `editorData.ts` — Pages, links, themes (`pagesData`, `Page`, `Link`)
- `linkData.ts` — Link types and detailed mock links (`LinkData`, `mockLinks`)

**State management** uses React Context in `components/editor/shared/`:
- `EditorThemeContext.tsx` — Theme/styling
- `LinksContext.tsx` — Links data
- `ProfileHeaderContext.tsx` — Profile header

## Guidelines

Read files in `agent-rules/` BEFORE implementing if the task involves their domain:

| File                     | When to read                                            |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| `ARBOR.mdc`              | Typography, colors, shadows, Arbor tokens over Tailwind |
| `FIGMA.mdc`              | Translating Figma designs to code                       |
| `web-best-practices.mdc` | Interactions, accessibility, animations, layout         |

## Key Patterns

- **Check before creating**: Search `shared/`, `link-block/`, `edit-block/`, `profile/`, and `ui/` before building new components
- **Arbor tokens first**: Prefer `text-body-sm`, `bg-primary`, `shadow-elevation-200` over raw Tailwind values
- **Use clsx for Arbor tokens**: The `cn()` helper strips custom `text-body-*` classes — use `clsx()` directly
- **Phosphor icons in IconButton**: Cast icons — `icon={PlusIcon as IconComponent}`

## Important

**Don't over-engineer** — stay focused on the task, ask questions until you have all the information you need.
